1
00:00:05,590 --> 00:00:06,758
Do you see them anywhere?

2
00:00:06,883 --> 00:00:09,719
Why don't we go back to their house,
wait for them there?

3
00:00:09,844 --> 00:00:12,430
Yeah, because they'll
probably answer the door

4
00:00:12,555 --> 00:00:14,307
the 16th time I knock.

5
00:00:23,191 --> 00:00:24,609
There they are.

6
00:00:27,654 --> 00:00:30,407
Hi. I'm sorry
I followed you here.

7
00:00:30,532 --> 00:00:33,052
I just really wish you could give me
a few minutes of your time.

8
00:00:35,620 --> 00:00:37,914
I know you never agreed
to make it an open adoption,

9
00:00:38,039 --> 00:00:39,999
but I just figured
maybe you never had a choice.

10
00:00:40,125 --> 00:00:41,710
I mean, it's China, right?

11
00:00:49,843 --> 00:00:53,012
- What did he say?
- He wants you to leave them alone.

12
00:00:56,224 --> 00:00:57,475
Please.

13
00:00:58,852 --> 00:01:00,770
I just want 10 minutes.

14
00:01:00,895 --> 00:01:02,814
Learn what you're like,
tell you about my life.

15
00:01:14,117 --> 00:01:16,870
He said they have no daughter.

16
00:01:18,246 --> 00:01:20,665
I am sorry you wasted a trip.

17
00:01:21,791 --> 00:01:23,293
I know that's them.

18
00:01:26,671 --> 00:01:28,047
How does that work?

19
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:34,262
How do I pray?

20
00:01:34,387 --> 00:01:36,723
You make a wish
and lift the Buddha.

21
00:01:41,770 --> 00:01:45,315
I wish they could understand
how badly I need this.

22
00:01:56,367 --> 00:01:58,578
Now make the wish again.

23
00:01:58,703 --> 00:02:01,998
If you cannot lift the Buddha this time,
your wish will be granted.

24
00:02:14,886 --> 00:02:16,179
Are you okay?

25
00:02:59,347 --> 00:03:03,017
Picked Cameron's pocket down in the ER.
Came up with a doozy.

26
00:03:03,142 --> 00:03:04,811
Your mother called. Twice.

27
00:03:04,936 --> 00:03:08,231
But she's still healthy. This
25-year-old woman, on the other hand...

28
00:03:08,356 --> 00:03:10,149
Her messages sounded
kind of urgent.

29
00:03:10,275 --> 00:03:13,987
Well, that's the way women sound
when their spouse of 50 years dies.

30
00:03:17,866 --> 00:03:19,909
Your dad died? Are you...

31
00:03:20,034 --> 00:03:22,579
Yep, fine. Our patient,

32
00:03:22,704 --> 00:03:25,582
who's been known to take
a few drinks on non-occasions,

33
00:03:25,707 --> 00:03:28,751
vomits blood and collapses
on a trip to China.

34
00:03:28,877 --> 00:03:31,254
Chinese surgeons cut
out a foot of bowel,

35
00:03:31,379 --> 00:03:33,256
but the pain is worse
now than it was before.

36
00:03:33,381 --> 00:03:35,049
House, call your mom.

37
00:03:35,174 --> 00:03:36,593
What are you, my mom?

38
00:03:37,218 --> 00:03:39,637
We can continue
this differential in five minutes.

39
00:03:39,762 --> 00:03:43,391
Are those bags under your eyes?
You were up all night.

40
00:03:43,516 --> 00:03:44,642
You told her, didn't you?

41
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:49,397
I don't know what your daddy issues are,
but don't deflect them on me.

42
00:03:49,522 --> 00:03:51,566
Told his wife
he's been getting some strange.

43
00:03:51,691 --> 00:03:54,027
She kicked
his adulterous tuchus to the curb.

44
00:03:54,152 --> 00:03:55,112
Seriously? You told her?

45
00:03:55,236 --> 00:03:56,613
Yes, I told her,

46
00:03:56,738 --> 00:03:58,406
but, no, she did not
kick me to the curb.

47
00:03:58,531 --> 00:04:00,909
We stayed up late talking.
We're going to continue talking.

48
00:04:01,034 --> 00:04:03,703
Much like House should be doing
with his mother right now.

49
00:04:03,828 --> 00:04:05,705
Anybody read Chinese?

50
00:04:05,830 --> 00:04:08,082
Otherwise, we have no idea
what these doctors did to her.

51
00:04:08,207 --> 00:04:12,128
Kutner, you're sort of Asian, right?
Get it translated.

52
00:04:12,253 --> 00:04:13,922
What about Meckel's diverticulum?

53
00:04:14,047 --> 00:04:15,924
If the surgeons didn't remove
the diverticulum,

54
00:04:16,049 --> 00:04:17,884
it could cause pain, bleeding.

55
00:04:18,009 --> 00:04:19,802
Too high up for a colonoscopy.

56
00:04:19,928 --> 00:04:22,597
CT could miss it.
Ultrasound's fastest.

57
00:04:22,722 --> 00:04:24,349
And since I'm the fastest
with the ultrasound...

58
00:04:24,474 --> 00:04:26,851
House.
Let me do the ultrasound.

59
00:04:26,976 --> 00:04:28,616
You need to deal
with your dad and stop...

60
00:04:28,686 --> 00:04:31,522
I'm not deflecting
because I'm avoiding something deep.

61
00:04:31,648 --> 00:04:34,484
I'm deflecting
because I'm avoiding something shallow.

62
00:04:34,609 --> 00:04:37,695
Seriously, I'm fine.
I didn't even like the man.

63
00:04:41,741 --> 00:04:43,451
No Meckel's.

64
00:04:43,576 --> 00:04:46,663
You there for the rice
or the re-education camps?

65
00:04:46,788 --> 00:04:49,123
I was there to track down
my biological parents.

66
00:04:49,248 --> 00:04:52,502
Like a salmon returning
to the stream where it was born.

67
00:04:52,627 --> 00:04:55,129
Did you become whole again
or did you get eaten by bears?

68
00:04:55,254 --> 00:04:57,215
They denied my existence.

69
00:05:00,551 --> 00:05:03,721
Four parents and not one of them
taught you to cover your mouth.

70
00:05:03,846 --> 00:05:07,308
My God, it looks like
they cut you in half.

71
00:05:07,433 --> 00:05:09,102
Doctor, we're her parents,
I'm...

72
00:05:09,227 --> 00:05:10,687
I'm just a technician.

73
00:05:10,812 --> 00:05:12,852
Her doctors will be by later,
you can schmooze then.

74
00:05:12,939 --> 00:05:15,817
Can you let them know
that we went by her apartment,

75
00:05:15,942 --> 00:05:18,319
collected all her medications...

76
00:05:19,153 --> 00:05:20,863
I'm a technician and a doctor.

77
00:05:20,989 --> 00:05:22,407
You went through my apartment?

78
00:05:22,532 --> 00:05:25,743
We found alcohol.
We thought you'd quit.

79
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,912
- Did her drinking cause this?
- No.

80
00:05:30,123 --> 00:05:31,457
Can you tell her it did?

81
00:05:39,757 --> 00:05:41,259
Licorice root.

82
00:05:42,593 --> 00:05:44,762
No, thanks, I'm good.

83
00:05:44,887 --> 00:05:47,682
I threw it to you for a reason.

84
00:05:47,807 --> 00:05:51,477
It's what the Chinese doctors gave her.
It contains glycyrrhizin.

85
00:05:51,602 --> 00:05:54,313
They were treating her for SARS?

86
00:05:54,439 --> 00:05:58,735
Not very effectively.
But SARS explains the cough,

87
00:05:58,860 --> 00:06:02,238
causes hypoperfusion, which explains
the ischemic bowel. It's perfect.

88
00:06:02,363 --> 00:06:04,115
Lung involvement
isn't very severe.

89
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,993
Okay, well, so call it ARS.

90
00:06:07,118 --> 00:06:09,287
Start her on ribavirin
and interferon.

91
00:06:17,628 --> 00:06:19,714
I'm sorry about your father.

92
00:06:19,839 --> 00:06:20,673
I'm not.

93
00:06:22,008 --> 00:06:24,135
Are we done emoting now?

94
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:25,803
If there's anything
I can do, just...

95
00:06:25,928 --> 00:06:29,307
You know, you're right.
I don't think I can sleep alone tonight.

96
00:06:31,184 --> 00:06:33,644
Tell me that is liquid Vicodin.

97
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:35,229
We're giving IG shots
to everyone

98
00:06:35,354 --> 00:06:37,065
who came in contact
with your patient.

99
00:06:37,190 --> 00:06:41,069
Shockingly, none of the nurses
volunteered to administer yours.

100
00:06:42,528 --> 00:06:44,322
It goes better
in a large muscle.

101
00:06:45,323 --> 00:06:46,574
Drop your pants.

102
00:06:46,699 --> 00:06:51,245
You know, I usually pay
tens of dollars to hear that.

103
00:06:57,835 --> 00:06:58,920
The funeral's tomorrow.

104
00:06:59,045 --> 00:07:00,254
My mom called you?

105
00:07:00,379 --> 00:07:03,299
There is a 3:40 flight
out of Newark.

106
00:07:03,424 --> 00:07:06,928
If you leave now,
you can be in Lexington tonight.

107
00:07:07,053 --> 00:07:09,013
Your mother wants you
to deliver a eulogy.

108
00:07:09,138 --> 00:07:12,517
Eulogy, from the Greek
for "good word."

109
00:07:13,017 --> 00:07:16,646
Now if she'd asked me to deliver
a bastardogy, I'd be happy to...

110
00:07:16,771 --> 00:07:19,398
Then be a grownup.
Call your mother back

111
00:07:19,524 --> 00:07:21,734
and tell her
you're sick with grief,

112
00:07:21,859 --> 00:07:23,099
but you're too busy
to be there.

113
00:07:23,194 --> 00:07:24,695
She knows when I'm lying.

114
00:07:24,821 --> 00:07:26,405
Then start writing.

115
00:07:34,288 --> 00:07:36,707
I yanked my
brother and sister out of college?

116
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,752
Can you please tell them
I'm not dying?

117
00:07:39,877 --> 00:07:42,463
You have SARS.
I'm wearing a mask.

118
00:07:42,588 --> 00:07:45,091
It's a big deal.
Cut them some slack.

119
00:07:45,216 --> 00:07:46,843
But I am going
to be okay, right?

120
00:07:46,968 --> 00:07:49,053
That's what all
this stuff is for.

121
00:07:49,178 --> 00:07:50,658
We're gonna need
the names and numbers

122
00:07:50,763 --> 00:07:51,931
of everyone you came
in contact with

123
00:07:52,056 --> 00:07:54,892
here and in China.
Flight numbers, dates.

124
00:07:55,017 --> 00:07:58,271
That doctor that I coughed all over,
is he gonna be all right?

125
00:07:58,396 --> 00:08:00,022
So far, he's fine.

126
00:08:11,409 --> 00:08:15,705
It's back.
This is where the pain all started.

127
00:08:16,831 --> 00:08:19,208
She's tachycardia.
Get a crash cart in here!

128
00:08:21,085 --> 00:08:22,837
What's going on?

129
00:08:22,962 --> 00:08:25,256
I need to know what's going on.
That's my daughter.

130
00:08:29,343 --> 00:08:31,846
Her liver's failing.
It's not SARS.

131
00:08:51,282 --> 00:08:54,118
I am not doing this
because I care.

132
00:09:03,836 --> 00:09:06,839
Cuddy drugged me. She...

133
00:09:10,509 --> 00:09:14,180
My mom didn't call Cuddy.
She called you.

134
00:09:15,723 --> 00:09:18,976
I knew you couldn't stay away.
I knew you loved me too much.

135
00:09:19,101 --> 00:09:20,603
I'm doing this for your mom.

136
00:09:20,728 --> 00:09:22,480
I'm not doing this at all.

137
00:09:22,605 --> 00:09:23,564
If there was something
to be done,

138
00:09:23,689 --> 00:09:26,067
I would have done it
in the year he spent dying.

139
00:09:27,485 --> 00:09:29,320
You took my Vicodin?

140
00:09:31,072 --> 00:09:32,240
I'm in pain.

141
00:09:39,872 --> 00:09:40,790
One?

142
00:09:43,793 --> 00:09:47,046
So the Vicodin is my leash.
One will take the edge off,

143
00:09:47,171 --> 00:09:48,297
but it won't give me
enough relief

144
00:09:48,422 --> 00:09:50,424
for an escape
back to Plainsboro.

145
00:09:57,598 --> 00:09:59,183
Where's my phone?

146
00:10:01,185 --> 00:10:03,604
It's the team,
it's their ring tone.

147
00:10:05,982 --> 00:10:08,818
Forget it.
The patient's blood is on your hands.

148
00:10:15,324 --> 00:10:17,618
<i>House? You there?</i>

149
00:10:17,743 --> 00:10:19,495
I'm being held against my will.
Call the police.

150
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:21,289
Nicole had a clot
in the hepatic vein.

151
00:10:21,414 --> 00:10:22,873
Chase sucked it out,
saved her liver.

152
00:10:22,999 --> 00:10:25,167
No signs of a tumor
or venous malformations,

153
00:10:25,293 --> 00:10:26,794
- nothing that could cause...
- She's an addict.

154
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:29,005
- Drugs and alcohol wouldn't...
- She's a smoker.

155
00:10:29,130 --> 00:10:31,716
Combine smoking with
any one of a dozen genetic disorders

156
00:10:31,841 --> 00:10:33,001
and she's a clotting machine.

157
00:10:33,092 --> 00:10:34,427
Multiple blood clots
would tie together

158
00:10:34,552 --> 00:10:36,178
bowel ischemia,
lungs and the liver.

159
00:10:36,304 --> 00:10:38,180
<i>We need to pinpoint
which defect she has</i>

160
00:10:38,306 --> 00:10:40,349
so <i>we can start her
on the right anti-coagulant.</i>

161
00:10:40,474 --> 00:10:41,434
Draw blood.

162
00:10:41,559 --> 00:10:44,395
Let's find out which genetic gift
her genetic parents gave her.

163
00:10:45,855 --> 00:10:47,481
Thanks for calling.

164
00:10:49,608 --> 00:10:52,987
My ring tone for you
is Dancing Queen by Abba.

165
00:10:59,952 --> 00:11:01,037
Nicole?

166
00:11:04,373 --> 00:11:06,625
I need to pee.
Pull over at the next stop.

167
00:11:11,714 --> 00:11:13,132
I'll just pee on the floor.

168
00:11:15,426 --> 00:11:20,097
You bought used floor mats?
That is brilliant.

169
00:11:22,683 --> 00:11:25,186
There's a rest stop
in five miles.

170
00:11:39,283 --> 00:11:41,118
- Cane.
- The restroom's right there.

171
00:11:41,243 --> 00:11:42,787
You can make it on your own.

172
00:11:47,124 --> 00:11:48,918
I suppose I could
talk about the summer

173
00:11:49,043 --> 00:11:50,961
he decided
he wasn't speaking to me.

174
00:11:51,087 --> 00:11:53,798
Two months. Not one word.

175
00:11:53,923 --> 00:11:56,217
Anything he wanted to say,
he typed up

176
00:11:56,342 --> 00:11:58,928
and slipped under
my bedroom door.

177
00:11:59,053 --> 00:12:02,014
You don't want to say anything,
don't say anything, but go.

178
00:12:02,139 --> 00:12:04,642
Tell your mom you're sad.
For her.

179
00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:06,644
Just by being there
I'd be lying.

180
00:12:06,769 --> 00:12:10,439
She wants to think, for a moment,
that she had a happy family.

181
00:12:10,564 --> 00:12:13,484
So give her a gift. Lie.

182
00:12:13,609 --> 00:12:17,696
Give me my cane,
I'll go to the damn funeral.

183
00:12:38,759 --> 00:12:41,846
I said I'd go to the funeral.
I didn't say when.

184
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:50,438
We have these two categories,
inside and outside.

185
00:12:50,563 --> 00:12:53,065
Patients stay inside,
then, when they're better,

186
00:12:53,190 --> 00:12:54,733
we let them go outside.

187
00:12:54,859 --> 00:12:57,945
Thanks, but they don't
let you smoke inside.

188
00:12:58,070 --> 00:12:59,613
So why don't you go back there

189
00:12:59,738 --> 00:13:02,158
and give me five minutes outside?

190
00:13:10,583 --> 00:13:12,209
Make a fist.

191
00:13:18,424 --> 00:13:21,886
Such a beautiful day, we thought
we'd do all our doctoring outside.

192
00:13:22,845 --> 00:13:26,557
People stare at me
any time I'm out with my family.

193
00:13:26,682 --> 00:13:29,810
It's like a puzzle. Which one
of these things doesn't belong?

194
00:13:29,935 --> 00:13:31,770
Belonging is overrated.

195
00:13:32,938 --> 00:13:35,399
I was adopted by a white family
when I was nine.

196
00:13:36,066 --> 00:13:40,446
I like being different. The view's
better from the outside looking in.

197
00:13:44,325 --> 00:13:48,245
Must be easier to be different
when you're a success.

198
00:13:50,289 --> 00:13:51,582
Is that a problem?

199
00:13:51,707 --> 00:13:54,043
This is why we prefer inside.

200
00:14:05,179 --> 00:14:06,430
You actually keep a flashlight

201
00:14:06,555 --> 00:14:08,682
that doesn't need batteries
in the trunk?

202
00:14:08,807 --> 00:14:11,977
Next to the jacket,
emergency water,

203
00:14:12,102 --> 00:14:14,939
nail clippers,
toothbrush, space blanket.

204
00:14:15,064 --> 00:14:16,982
When things go wrong,
I like to be ready.

205
00:14:18,692 --> 00:14:21,779
Will you please hold the flashlight
for a minute?

206
00:14:34,083 --> 00:14:36,627
You know, those aren't
just my car keys.

207
00:14:36,752 --> 00:14:38,837
My house keys
are on there, too.

208
00:14:38,963 --> 00:14:40,589
Amber gave me that key chain.

209
00:14:40,714 --> 00:14:42,216
No, she didn't.

210
00:14:42,341 --> 00:14:44,760
Not unless your pet name
for her was "Volvo."

211
00:14:53,644 --> 00:14:57,273
A man who would lie about a gift
from his dead girlfriend...

212
00:14:57,398 --> 00:15:01,777
ls probably responding to a childish,
pointless act of petulance.

213
00:15:01,902 --> 00:15:04,613
The struggle to resist one's captors
is never pointless.

214
00:15:07,241 --> 00:15:11,287
Well, I hate to break it to you, Che,
but simple delay won't work.

215
00:15:11,412 --> 00:15:14,039
Your mother will hold the funeral
till we get there.

216
00:15:15,708 --> 00:15:19,753
My father was a punctual man,
beholden to time.

217
00:15:19,878 --> 00:15:22,715
Two minutes late for dinner,
you didn't eat.

218
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:26,260
My mother would never disrespect him
by starting the funeral late.

219
00:15:26,427 --> 00:15:30,556
Yeah, you clearly have no issues
to work through.

220
00:15:30,973 --> 00:15:34,143
Come on, forget the keys.
Call a locksmith.

221
00:15:34,268 --> 00:15:35,894
We'll go inside
and play Guess that Smell

222
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:38,314
with the truckers
while we're waiting.

223
00:15:38,439 --> 00:15:39,857
Join me on the dark side.

224
00:15:41,692 --> 00:15:43,944
Dark side's done, House.

225
00:15:44,069 --> 00:15:46,655
I'm delivering you to your mother,
and that's it.

226
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:50,200
I've moved on.

227
00:15:54,288 --> 00:15:55,649
What do you think
House would send?

228
00:15:55,664 --> 00:15:59,835
The Gentle Comfort arrangement
or the Warm Thoughts bouquet?

229
00:16:00,544 --> 00:16:03,213
I mean, if he wasn't an ass.

230
00:16:03,339 --> 00:16:06,550
Send one of those giant cookies
shaped like a coffin.

231
00:16:07,426 --> 00:16:09,053
His mom would believe
it was from him.

232
00:16:09,178 --> 00:16:11,013
I didn't tell you
so you could send anything.

233
00:16:11,138 --> 00:16:12,459
Just wanted you to know
the extent

234
00:16:12,514 --> 00:16:14,600
to which the man is disconnected
from the human race.

235
00:16:14,725 --> 00:16:17,102
Took a six pack of FFP
to stop the oozing.

236
00:16:17,227 --> 00:16:18,395
She's bleeding and clotting?

237
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:20,606
Plus schistocytes on her smear
means it's DIC,

238
00:16:20,731 --> 00:16:21,649
which means she's got cancer.

239
00:16:21,774 --> 00:16:23,108
She's young.
It could be leukemia.

240
00:16:23,233 --> 00:16:25,194
Normal WBC
makes that less likely.

241
00:16:25,319 --> 00:16:26,737
Belly pain points
toward a GI tumor.

242
00:16:26,862 --> 00:16:27,946
House already
did an ultrasound.

243
00:16:28,072 --> 00:16:30,824
He wasn't looking for a tumor.
Go run a CT.

244
00:16:31,367 --> 00:16:32,701
