339
00:21:12,147 --> 00:21:13,565
Clears things.

340
00:21:14,566 --> 00:21:16,610
It's a waste of time.

341
00:21:25,285 --> 00:21:27,245
I need that phone call.

342
00:21:27,996 --> 00:21:29,373
I'm a doctor.

343
00:21:29,498 --> 00:21:32,709
When someone tries to call you
three times, it's code for.

344
00:21:32,834 --> 00:21:35,087
"Pick up the damn phone
before someone dies."

345
00:21:35,212 --> 00:21:37,506
I'm sure there's other
smart doctors.

346
00:21:37,631 --> 00:21:39,091
You'd be surprised.

347
00:21:40,175 --> 00:21:41,885
You told me you'd
taken care of this.

348
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:43,470
I did.

349
00:21:43,595 --> 00:21:45,639
The first words
you ever said to me.

350
00:21:45,764 --> 00:21:47,683
I took care of it.

351
00:21:47,808 --> 00:21:49,601
You must have
screwed up somehow.

352
00:21:50,811 --> 00:21:56,525
Sir? Not to hurry you,
but we need to be at a funeral in...

353
00:21:56,650 --> 00:21:59,695
Nobody is going anywhere
or taking any phone calls

354
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:01,780
till I hear back
from Louisiana.

355
00:22:01,905 --> 00:22:03,949
It's a really old warrant.

356
00:22:04,074 --> 00:22:06,394
Isn't there a statute of limitations
on this kind of thing?

357
00:22:06,451 --> 00:22:09,162
It's suspended
when you flee the state.

358
00:22:09,287 --> 00:22:12,833
I didn't flee the state,
I left the state,

359
00:22:12,958 --> 00:22:14,668
because I don't
live in the state.

360
00:22:14,793 --> 00:22:18,839
And the charges were
just so minor...

361
00:22:18,964 --> 00:22:22,801
"Vandalism,
destruction of property, assault..."

362
00:22:22,926 --> 00:22:25,178
There is a simple explanation.

363
00:22:25,303 --> 00:22:27,514
There was a medical convention
in New Orleans.

364
00:22:27,639 --> 00:22:29,433
You don't need
to explain to me.

365
00:22:29,558 --> 00:22:30,758
I was fresh out of med school.

366
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:32,328
I didn't know anybody
at the convention.

367
00:22:32,436 --> 00:22:35,522
You heard the man, Wilson.
You don't have to explain.

368
00:22:35,647 --> 00:22:37,566
I am not going to sit here
wasting time

369
00:22:37,691 --> 00:22:40,235
just so you can avoid
your father's funeral.

370
00:22:42,612 --> 00:22:44,114
He's my father.

371
00:22:44,531 --> 00:22:46,408
I have the right
to avoid his funeral.

372
00:22:46,533 --> 00:22:48,243
Not if your mother's alive,
you don't.

373
00:22:49,870 --> 00:22:52,914
Okay. Explain.

374
00:22:53,999 --> 00:22:55,876
Did House react
to the eight centimeters?

375
00:22:56,001 --> 00:22:58,920
He whistled. It's huge.
Anyone would think so.

376
00:22:59,046 --> 00:23:01,089
House doesn't whistle
because he's impressed.

377
00:23:01,214 --> 00:23:03,091
Means he wasn't expecting it.

378
00:23:03,216 --> 00:23:05,385
Means he changed his mind
at that point.

379
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:08,180
A single super-sized cyst
ruled out a diffuse process,

380
00:23:08,305 --> 00:23:09,681
like scleroderma or lupus.

381
00:23:09,806 --> 00:23:11,475
Rule out diffuse process,
you're stuck with single process,

382
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:13,185
affecting just the pancreas.

383
00:23:13,310 --> 00:23:15,312
Gallstones
or pancreatic divisum.

384
00:23:15,437 --> 00:23:17,355
Whatever he asked next
would have narrowed that down.

385
00:23:17,481 --> 00:23:18,565
He asked about location.

386
00:23:18,690 --> 00:23:20,609
Heads, it's gallstones.
Tails, it's divisum.

387
00:23:20,734 --> 00:23:22,944
It's at the head.
She's got gallstones.

388
00:23:23,070 --> 00:23:24,696
The steamroller means
potholes, means...

389
00:23:24,821 --> 00:23:26,490
Relax. We got it.

390
00:23:26,615 --> 00:23:28,617
You figured out
she's got gallstones?

391
00:23:31,244 --> 00:23:35,457
I was at the hotel bar,
trying to unwind with a drink.

392
00:23:35,582 --> 00:23:38,710
There was this guy
who kept playing

393
00:23:38,835 --> 00:23:42,214
Billy Joel's <i>Leave</i>
a Tender Moment Alone on the jukebox.

394
00:23:42,339 --> 00:23:44,049
<i>Leave a Tender Moment
is a good song.</i>

395
00:23:44,174 --> 00:23:46,176
It's a great song.
He was out of line.

396
00:23:46,301 --> 00:23:48,678
<i>Not as good as Scenes
from an Italian Restaurant or...</i>

397
00:23:48,804 --> 00:23:52,724
So I asked the man to stop.
Politely.

398
00:23:52,849 --> 00:23:54,726
Yeah, you yelled politely.

399
00:23:54,851 --> 00:23:56,937
I was polite
the first couple of times.

400
00:23:57,062 --> 00:24:00,524
But courtesy made no impression
on this ass.

401
00:24:00,649 --> 00:24:05,737
So I threw a bottle
into the mirror,

402
00:24:05,862 --> 00:24:08,657
which successfully
conveyed my message.

403
00:24:08,782 --> 00:24:11,493
And smashed
a 10-foot antique mirror.

404
00:24:11,618 --> 00:24:14,955
And set an example for two
other patrons, who threw shot glasses...

405
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:17,165
I had nothing
to do with that fight.

406
00:24:17,290 --> 00:24:19,501
The assault charge
was totally bogus.

407
00:24:19,626 --> 00:24:22,087
And I paid for the mirror.

408
00:24:22,212 --> 00:24:23,547
I think I have the picture.

409
00:24:25,006 --> 00:24:27,968
I assume you're the guy
who was playing the song.

410
00:24:28,093 --> 00:24:30,470
No, I was the guy
who bailed him out.

411
00:24:30,595 --> 00:24:33,181
That's how we met.
I was in jail.

412
00:24:33,306 --> 00:24:36,476
This guy was a total stranger to you,
and you bailed him out?

413
00:24:36,601 --> 00:24:38,436
It was a boring convention.

414
00:24:38,562 --> 00:24:40,272
I had to have somebody
to drink with.

415
00:24:40,397 --> 00:24:42,649
And there's the foundation
of our entire friendship.

416
00:24:42,774 --> 00:24:45,694
If you hadn't been bored one weekend,
it wouldn't even exist.

417
00:24:45,819 --> 00:24:48,738
Hey, with 3,000 people
at that convention,

418
00:24:48,864 --> 00:24:50,991
you were the one I thought
wasn't boring. That says something.

419
00:24:51,116 --> 00:24:53,493
It also says something that you lied
to me about getting the charges dropped.

420
00:24:53,618 --> 00:24:56,246
I got a lawyer, he cut a deal.
You didn't call the guy?

421
00:24:56,371 --> 00:24:58,915
You have to show up at the arraignment.
Everybody knows that.

422
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:01,793
Everybody
with your misdemeanor experience.

423
00:25:01,918 --> 00:25:03,753
You can go.

424
00:25:03,879 --> 00:25:04,963
What?

425
00:25:05,088 --> 00:25:07,757
He's a fugitive from justice.

426
00:25:07,883 --> 00:25:10,302
That whole story was lies.
He stabbed a man.

427
00:25:10,427 --> 00:25:14,014
Louisiana doesn't want to pay
to get you back.

428
00:25:14,139 --> 00:25:17,142
Forget Louisiana.
He was driving recklessly

429
00:25:17,267 --> 00:25:19,311
through your comatose village.

430
00:25:19,436 --> 00:25:21,646
What, do they put lead
in the jelly donuts here?

431
00:25:21,771 --> 00:25:23,565
Stop acting
like such an ingrate

432
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:26,109
and go pay your respects
to your father.

433
00:25:28,111 --> 00:25:30,530
CT confirmed gallstones.

434
00:25:30,947 --> 00:25:35,035
Normally not dangerous, almost everyone
has them, but sometimes...

435
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:36,328
They kill you?

436
00:25:36,453 --> 00:25:39,039
Yup. Unless I take them out.

437
00:25:39,164 --> 00:25:40,665
We do it laparoscopically.

438
00:25:42,626 --> 00:25:43,835
Um...

439
00:25:46,504 --> 00:25:48,381
How long has her urine
been brown?

440
00:25:48,506 --> 00:25:50,383
Kidneys were fine
this afternoon.

441
00:25:50,508 --> 00:25:51,843
They're not now.

442
00:25:53,929 --> 00:25:55,305
It's not the gallstones.

443
00:25:58,391 --> 00:26:00,602
Well, of course
it's not gallstones.

444
00:26:00,727 --> 00:26:01,978
Who thought it was gallstones?

445
00:26:02,103 --> 00:26:03,188
You said "steamroller."

446
00:26:03,313 --> 00:26:05,190
I also said
"construction site."

447
00:26:05,315 --> 00:26:07,943
Gallstones could cause
a pancreatic cyst.

448
00:26:08,068 --> 00:26:11,154
Just turn around.
The thing is two hours over already,

449
00:26:11,279 --> 00:26:13,156
and that's the third time
we've passed that colonial

450
00:26:13,281 --> 00:26:15,325
with the cross
burning out front.

451
00:26:15,450 --> 00:26:16,785
I'm not lost.

452
00:26:17,702 --> 00:26:19,412
I'm not talking about
what caused the cyst.

453
00:26:19,537 --> 00:26:21,289
I'm talking about
what the cyst caused.

454
00:26:21,414 --> 00:26:22,249
<i>Everything-</i>

455
00:26:22,374 --> 00:26:24,209
Cysts are symptoms,
not diagnoses.

456
00:26:24,334 --> 00:26:27,921
Unless it's a multiple cyst
with connections to other organs.

457
00:26:28,046 --> 00:26:29,256
Like a steamroller.

458
00:26:29,381 --> 00:26:31,383
That's a long road
down to the kidneys.

459
00:26:31,508 --> 00:26:33,885
How do we prove it?
Won't be visible on a scan,

460
00:26:34,010 --> 00:26:35,512
Chase isn't gonna go
groping around

461
00:26:35,637 --> 00:26:36,797
when she's got kidney failure.

462
00:26:36,805 --> 00:26:37,889
Bubbles.

463
00:26:38,014 --> 00:26:40,058
- Is that your new stripper name?
- Yes.

464
00:26:40,183 --> 00:26:42,978
And also, we inject bubbles into
the cyst and follow where they drift.

465
00:26:43,103 --> 00:26:44,104
If they end up in her other organs,

466
00:26:44,229 --> 00:26:46,022
we know you're right,
cut it out, she's fine.

467
00:26:46,147 --> 00:26:48,233
Bubbles is right. Go echo.

468
00:26:51,278 --> 00:26:52,737
I'm not lost.

469
00:27:09,629 --> 00:27:11,423
Nicole, you gotta stay still.

470
00:27:11,548 --> 00:27:12,841
I'm nervous.

471
00:27:12,966 --> 00:27:15,844
You're not nervous.
It's the DTs, isn't it?

472
00:27:17,470 --> 00:27:20,473
I haven't had a drink
since I got here.

473
00:27:22,684 --> 00:27:25,895
Good heavens.
We haven't missed it after all.

474
00:27:26,021 --> 00:27:27,939
It's like the end of
<i>A</i> Christmas Carol.

475
00:27:39,784 --> 00:27:41,369
I'm so glad you're here.

476
00:27:42,954 --> 00:27:46,791
It's a load off of my mind
just to see you.

477
00:27:49,044 --> 00:27:50,170
Thank you, James.

478
00:27:50,295 --> 00:27:52,047
Mom, how could you
delay the funeral?

479
00:27:52,172 --> 00:27:55,633
Honey, your dad is dead.
He's not going to care.

480
00:27:55,759 --> 00:27:57,510
Do you know what
you're going to say?

481
00:27:57,635 --> 00:27:59,763
I don't know.
Just let the minister,

482
00:27:59,888 --> 00:28:01,556
or one of his buddies
from the Corps...

483
00:28:01,681 --> 00:28:02,849
You're talking.

484
00:28:02,974 --> 00:28:04,976
I don't care
that you didn't like him.

485
00:28:05,101 --> 00:28:07,771
He was your father
and he loved you.

486
00:28:08,355 --> 00:28:10,273
The war is over, Greg.

487
00:28:11,775 --> 00:28:13,735
Please do this for me.

488
00:28:16,613 --> 00:28:18,907
Stop looking so worried.

489
00:28:20,075 --> 00:28:22,702
I know he's gonna
